text.paragraph:
The recommended maximum dosage of phentermine hydrochloride tablet is 15 mg daily for patients with severe renal impairment (eGFR 15 to 29 mL/min/1.73m2). Avoid use of phentermine hydrochloride tablet in patients with eGFR less than 15 mL/min/1.73m2 or end-stage renal disease requiring dialysis [see 
                              Use in Specific Populations (8.6) and Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)
                           ]

list.item:
Pregnancy [see 
                           Use in Specific Populations (8.1)
                        ]

Nursing [see 
                           Use in Specific Populations (8.3)
                        ]

text.paragraph:
Requirements may be altered [see 
                              Warnings and Precautions (5.9)
                           ].

Systemic exposure of phentermine may increase up to 91%, 45%, and 22% in patients with severe, moderate, and mild renal impairment, respectively [see
                              Dosage and Administration (2.2)and Use in Specific Populations (8.6)
                           ].

list.item:
Development of primary pulmonary hypertension [see 
                           Warnings and Precautions (5.2)
                        ]

Effects on the ability to engage in potentially hazardous tasks [see 

                              Warnings and Precautions (5.5)

                        ]

The risk of an increase in blood pressure [see
Warnings and Precautions (5.8) and Adverse Reactions (6)
]

The risk of interactions [see
Contraindications (4) , Warnings and Precautions (5) and Drug Interactions (7)
]

the potential for developing tolerance and actions if they suspect development of tolerance [see 

                              Warnings and Precautions (5.4)

                        ] and

the risk of dependence and the potential consequences of abuse [see
Warnings and Precautions (5.6) , Drug Abuse and Dependence (9), and Overdosage (10)
].
